-- Saudi Arabia to Create Mining Industrial Zone in North, SPA Says
-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 2012-02-20T14:24:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-20/saudi-arabia-to-create-mining-industrial-zone-in-north-spa-says.html
Saudi Arabia will create an
industrial zone for mining companies in the north, the official
 Saudi Press Agency  reported, citing a cabinet statement.  The government will allocate 290 square kilometers of land
for project and another 150 square kilometers nearby to build a
phosphate unit for  Saudi Arabian Mining Co. (MAADEN) , SPA said.  Saudi Arabian Railway Co.  and the Public Investment Fund
will build a railway line linking the zone to the rail network,
SPA said.  Saudi Electricity Co. (SECO) , the kingdom’s largest utility, will
get state funding to link the zone with the country’s high-
voltage electricity network, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
